  <static seed="1480" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalLiteralEquations/LiteralEquation290.pg">
    <statement><p>Solve this equation for <m>B</m>:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ \frac{1}{p} = \frac{6}{B+7} }</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="7" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>B = 6p-7</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To solve this equation, we multiple both sides with the common denominator <m>{p\mathopen{}\left(B+7\right)}</m>:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   \frac{1}{p} \amp = \frac{6}{B+7}   \\
   \frac{1}{p} \cdot p(B+7) \amp = \frac{6}{B+7} \cdot p(B+7) \\
   B+7 \amp = 6p \\
   B \amp = 6p - 7
\end{aligned}
}</m></p>
</solution>
